description: Margaret Thatcher, born a grocer’s daughter, entered politics in her early 20s, and despite initial setbacks she became one of the most influential figures of the 20th century.
title: Margaret Thatcher: Her Journey From Aspiring Politician to World Leader
title_page: Margaret Thatcher: Her Journey From Aspiring Politician to World Leader - The New York Times
maintext:
Slide 1 of 15,
Before she married Denis Thatcher, the future prime minister was Margaret Roberts, and she ran as a Conservative Party candidate for Parliament in 1950 — when, still in her mid-20s, she was the youngest woman to compete for a seat — and again in 1951. Although she did better than expected, she lost both times.
